# 0.1.0, 0.2.0: pre-0.3.0 experimental releases of the old yash-rs line,
# superseded long ago and not worth supporting. Floor the 0.x series at 0.3.0.
0.1.0
0.2.0

# 3.0.6: RECOVERED (see VERSIONS.md, iteration 8). yash-env's
# waker/queue.rs calls self.validate() unconditionally, but the validate
# method is gated #[cfg(debug_assertions)], so the --release build failed with
# error[E0599]: no method named `validate` ... &mut ScheduledWakerQueue. 3.0.5
# and 3.0.7 are unaffected (upstream gates the call sites there). The new
# patches/yashrs/3.0.6/001-waker-queue-release-validate.diff adds a
# #[cfg(not(debug_assertions))] no-op validate (release builds compile out the
# debug consistency check anyway), and shvr_build_yashrs now applies
# patches/yashrs/<v>/ like the other variants. No longer excluded.
